==Contention 2: Domestic Dependent Nations==&#xD;
&#xD;
&#xD;
====The status of Indian Tribes as domestic dependent nations codifies the dual character of the American subject: one that is colonial through the continuing legacy of manifest destiny and one that is anti-colonial as a product of revolution. ====&#xD;
**Bergland 2k **&#xD;
(Renee L. – prof English Simmons College; &amp;#34;The National Uncanny: Indian Ghosts and American Subjects&amp;#34;; Dartmouth UP; p. 12-4)&#xD;
